original: Callmander, Einar, praktiserande läkare, Göteborg, f. 13/6/07 i Sthlm av arkit. Ivar C. o. Ellen Davida Österberg. G. 36 m. Tyra Löwenthal. Barn: Ulla f. 39, Madeleine 46. — Stud:ex. i Sthlm 27, med. kand. i Lund 34, med. lic. v. Karol. inst. 38. Div. kort. för-ordn. v. Sthlms sjukh. 36-38, bitr. sjukh:läk. v. Garn:sjukh. i Skövde 39-41, prakt. läk. i Gbg. Bat:läk. i Fik res. 40, v. I. 9 40, v. A. 2 41, v. Lv 6 47.
translated: Callmander, Einar, practicing physician, Gothenburg, born June 13, 1907 in Stockholm to architect Ivar C. and Ellen Davida Österberg. Married in 1936 to Tyra Löwenthal. Children: Ulla, born in 1939 and Madeleine, born in 1946. He completed his high school education in Stockholm in 1927, received his Bachelor of Medicine degree in Lund in 1934, and his medical license from the Karolinska Institute in 1938. He served as a short-term locum at Stockholm Hospital from 1936 to 1938, assistant medical officer at the Garrison Hospital in Skövde from 1939 to 1941, and was a practicing physician in Gothenburg. He was a battalion physician in the Fik Regiment in 1940, and served with the I. 9 in 1940, A. 2 in 1941, and Lv 6 in 1947.
